My husband and I came across this restaurant and thought we should give it a try. We walked in only to find out that they were not accepting cards due to a system malfunction. We were told there was an ATM nearby. We were so hungry we decided to give it a try. We ordered the Molcajete Azteca, which came with shrimp, steak, chicken and a side of rice and beans reccomendation of our server. It was delicious! Probably the best molcajete I've ever had. The service however was not so great. Instead of being offered a complentary   appetizer due to the inconvenience, we were offered two sodas on the house. Sad I know. We also kept having to ask other servers passing by to assist our needs. They seemed very unorganized and not customer focused.

The food here is terrible. I had eaten there last year and the food was very bad. Last night I was hanging out with some friends and I said let's try that mexican restaurant even do I've eatean ther and the food was very bad but let's give it another try. Very bad idea. They just serve terrible old food. I ordered tacos and they brought me te tortilla taco only with meant and nothing else inside. My friend ordered a quesadilla and the flour tortilla tasted old. Another friend ordered a chimichanga and it tasted out of a box and microwaved. For all this bad food we ended up paying $128 for 4 people. Crapy food and expensive:(
Good food and great drinks! TVs for sports events. Great manager!

I have never been to a restaurant that I despise so much! The manager is an uneducated fool that knows nothing about customer service and really shouldn't be managing anything.  I'm sorry to say but I wouldn't go back to that place even if I was offered a free meal. The plates are dirty, you never get exactly what you ask for smh.

The service is terrible. We were given a dirty plate with a dead fly on it and when we told the waitress, she took the plate to exchange for another BUT rather than giving us a new plate, she came back with the same dirty plate that had dirty streak marks on it (and one of the dirt marks was left on there, she only removed the bug)!!  Also the menu says the Mexican burger comes with "guacamole" however this is not the case. I was given a small side plate with old avocado slices. Clearly, we were unsatisified.. The manager told us he would comp the meal.. As soon as we start eating he comes back to tell us we must pay! He couldn't make up his mind and all he wanted to do was argue and defend  his staff"s crappy service. It was just a bad experience and very uncomfortable, when you see this place, please keep driving!!

Waisted evening so far. Avoid this place at all costs.

Pros: convenient location to all the resorts in Sunny Isles. Quick delivery.  Cons: food is underwhelming. The Taraskas Soup was watery with no hint of any of the ingredients mentioned. The only decent food was the chips, but even the salsa was bland - just like tomato paste.  Would not recommend. Highly overpriced for the quality of the food.

I would choose zero stars if it was an option. The nachos were terrible. The cheese was cheez whiz and it was drenched with guacamole and sour cream. It took half an hour to get the food and 2 out of the 3 orders were wrong. We sent them back and it took another half an hour to get the food again. Wouldn't be surprised if it closed down tommorow.
Great place for some Mexican dishes with some quality drinks. Outdoor seating is available for those who are up for Miami's hummidty, and there was also live music playing the last time I was there.

caption: They messed up my order, PLUS they mixed it up with another pickup order. Enchiladas Suizas are supposed to be green sauce with cheese. It was drowned in red sauce and soggy by the time I got it. Not worth it. Also, NOT authentic beans and rice. Black beans for a Mexican joint?! Where are my refried? I had to drive back because they gave me the wrong bag-- it wasn't worth any of the hassle.
Restaurant was completely empty and they brought our food out completely cold. I would understand if it was busy!!!!!

Customer service is horrible. Made 3 orders for delivery at 2:20 PM, they said my food would arrive in 45minutes, by 3:37PM I still had no food. When I finally got it, it was a disappointment. Not only was my food cold but the description didn't match what the menu said. Dinner menu says 4 flautas, I got 3. The queso dip tasted horrible. When I called back the manager, didn't care to apologize for the delay. On top of that he said they're making changes to the menu, that's why I didn't get 4 flautas. He then said that he would pick up the food if I was disappointed. Needless to say I will never go or order from this place again.

Very bad food, menu is too small to read, manager is so rude, people are working there do no speak english very well, no matter what you ask they bring you whatever they want, so cheap in material. Never Want to go there again and 100% not recommended.

I just left after having a delicious lunch with my family. We were welcome by Zabdi, the nicest and most helpful manager. He recommended the steak covered in cheese and beans, we also tried tortilla soup, grilled fish tacos, chicken fingers for the kids, and chile relleno. Oh and a humongous guacamole, to die for. Very nice decoration and great prices.  We are definitely coming back ! Thank you! !

No stars period. We waited 10 minutes for a server to greet us. As we waited, we watched other customers be helped that arrived after us. We ordered "micheladas" with the bottle but were served draft. When we asked for it to be changed the "manager" came to our table and rudely stated we needed to ask for a bottle next time. Certain items on the menu were not worth the price (ceviche). We would ask the server for certain things and she never brought them. When asked to speak to the "manager" the bartender came and did not state his name or title just said he could help but in reality all he did was say sorry but didn't make the situtation better. He instead cleared the table and started cleaning the as we sat their. Overall horrible horrible horrible experience on our limited stay here in Miami. I definitely don't recommend this place unless you want service.

I came here for lunch break.  I was working around the area so I thought I would give it a try.  Service in general was acceptable.  The waitress was very cordial and attentive.  However the reason I'm writing this review is for the disgustingly, horrible "Chilaquiles" they claim in their menu which are the worst ones I have ever had.  I voice this to the waitress which was then communicated to the restaurant manager on duty.  He took my food and did not charge me for it, which was the right thing to do.  I may have had a bad experience this time around, perhaps next time will be better bit I doubt there will be one.
